<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-09T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-09T03:00:00-05:00" n="935" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d935">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.156/51: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-09T16:00:00+08:00">November 9, 1931—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 9—6:15 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>895. Legation’s 899 [<hi rend="italic">869</hi>], November 4, 11
                                a.m.<note n="70" xml:id="d935fn70">Not printed.</note> Regarding
                            foreshore regulations, Japanese Legation now informs me Japanese
                            Government not in a position to accept revised regulations.</p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>